deck: The greatest - and most terrible - technological achievement of Zenn-La
description:
The Illuminatrix is a magi-tech construction and the greatest technological achievement of the Zenn-Lavian people. It has the power to create the utopia that is Zenn-La on any world. It was soon realized that by doing this they were erasing the culture of worlds and forcing their ways on others.

The Illuminatrix was hidden and guarded by the Keeper of the Great Truth. Zenn-La stopped travelling the stars and over time it was forgotten.

After some time, Shalla Bal took the place of the Keeper and began forcing Zenn-Lavian culture across the universe. She was stopped by her former love the Silver Surfer who used his Power Cosmic to destroy the Illuminatrix and revert the worlds who had been converted back to their original state. But the consequence of this was Zenn-Lavian culture was completely wiped out and no trace of memory existed of the utopian society.

deck: An enchanted axe wielded by Artemis of the Bana-Migdhall
description:
Overview

Mistress is an enchanted axe that belongs to Artemis of the Bana Mighdall. At the age of sixteen, Artemis tried to claim a different weapon, but because such weapons choose their owners, she was rejected. At some point, that same weapon was lost, and Artemis left the Bana to find it. Because the weapon she felt was meant to own was gone, she settled on a weapon that did choose her; Mistress.

This weapon is extremely powerful. It is bulletproof, and Artemis wields it well enough that deflects bullets as well as Diana can with her bracelets. Mistress is also extremely powerful to the point that it can pierce the flesh of a Bizarro clone. However, there is one drawback to using Mistress. Artemis has a special connection to Mistress so that whenever the axe is damaged, Artemis experiences that damage as physical pain. Because the pain is not the result of physical injury, even small amounts of damage can cause Artemis to double over in pain despite her Amazonian durability.

deck: The Amulet of Power was an artifact created by Tarene's future self to empower a guardian of her choosing. Using this Amulet Desak became an all but unstoppable divine assassin capable of disposing potent gods or entire pantheons single handedly.
description:
History

The Jewel of The Designate was created via paradoxical cause and effect, from a stagnant Utopian future where Thor assumed the Odin Power and took reign of the Earth at the cost of independence and freewill. A betrayed and imprisoned Tarene, once upon being freed, enacts a scheme to create a protector in the past in order to safeguard her in the event the treacherous asgardians of her era would be dealt with accordingly.

One time about two centuries ago a humble & god fearing mortal named Desak Sterixian would sacrifice his beloved daughter in ceremonial tribute to their patron gods. When he refused to partake of the divine boon granted to him by the Spirit of the Jewel which was promised as protection from the wrath of his cruel, petty deities; it was only after his dear Almonnas' demise did he realize his mistake as the evil Kronnitt began laying siege to his home world. Inadvertently killing his wife and destorying his house and home in his rampage.

Now resigned to his abominable fate at the hands of his false idol, the spirit returned to him once more baring her gift after he realized his error. Incensed by the loss of his family, his home penultimately enraged at the callousness of divinity, Desak donned the Amulet gifted to him and was forever transformed.

Gone was the weak and meager man who fell victim to the wrath of higher beings, enter Desak; The Destoryer of Gods.

Powers

Transformation

  • Godlike Conditioning
    • Super Strength
    • Invulnerability
    • Super Speed & reflexes
    • Enhanced Stamina
    • Regenerative Healing Factor
    • Age Negation
    • Self-Sustenance

Divine Power Negation

Flight

  • Cosmic Awareness:

Divine Slaying

Divine Siphoning

  • Divine Force Manipulation:
    • Opric Blasts
    • Force Absorption/Redirection
    • Simulated Telekinesis
    • Concussive Force
    • Energy Infusion

Arms fabrication and amalgamation

  • Shield
  • Sword
  • Axe
  • Knife
  • The Destroyer
